summary.p: The STANDARD mode provides the latest recommended default values that should be safe to run in most scenarios
Note that the default values vended from this mode might change as best practices may evolve. As a result, it is encouraged to perform tests when upgrading the SDK
The IN_REGION mode builds on the standard mode and includes optimization tailored for applications which call AWS services from within the same AWS region
Note that the default values vended from this mode might change as best practices may evolve. As a result, it is encouraged to perform tests when upgrading the SDK
The CROSS_REGION mode builds on the standard mode and includes optimization tailored for applications which call AWS services in a different region
Note that the default values vended from this mode might change as best practices may evolve. As a result, it is encouraged to perform tests when upgrading the SDK
The MOBILE mode builds on the standard mode and includes optimization tailored for mobile applications
Note that the default values vended from this mode might change as best practices may evolve. As a result, it is encouraged to perform tests when upgrading the SDK
The AUTO mode is an experimental mode that builds on the standard mode. The SDK will attempt to discover the execution environment to determine the appropriate settings automatically.

Note that the auto detection is heuristics-based and does not guarantee 100% accuracy. STANDARD mode will be used if the execution environment cannot be determined. The auto detection might query EC2 Instance Metadata service, which might introduce latency. Therefore we recommend choosing an explicit defaults_mode instead if startup latency is critical to your application
The LEGACY mode provides default settings that vary per SDK and were used prior to establishment of defaults_mode

member.summary:

Maximum size (in bytes) a shard’s cache can reach before it starts rejecting writes. Must be greater than storageCacheSnapShotMemorySize and lower than instance’s total memory capacity. We recommend setting it to below 15% of the total memory capacity.

member.summary:

member.name: P:Amazon.TimestreamInfluxDB.Model.InfluxDBv2Parameters.StorageCacheSnapshotWriteColdDuration
member.summary:

Duration at which the storage engine will snapshot the cache and write it to a new TSM file if the shard hasn’t received writes or deletes.
Default: 10 minutes

member.name: P:Amazon.TimestreamInfluxDB.Model.InfluxDBv2Parameters.StorageCompactFullWriteColdDuration
member.summary:

Duration at which the storage engine will compact all TSM files in a shard if it hasn't received writes or deletes.
Default: 4 hours

member.summary:

Rate limit (in bytes per second) that TSM compactions can write to disk.
Default: 50331648

member.summary:

member.name: P:Amazon.TimestreamInfluxDB.Model.InfluxDBv2Parameters.StorageMaxIndexLogFileSize
member.summary:

Default: 1048576

member.name: P:Amazon.TimestreamInfluxDB.Model.InfluxDBv2Parameters.StorageNoValidateFieldSize
member.summary:

Skip field size validation on incoming write requests.
Default: false

member.name: P:Amazon.TimestreamInfluxDB.Model.InfluxDBv2Parameters.StorageRetentionCheckInterval
member.summary:

Interval of retention policy enforcement checks. Must be greater than 0.
Default: 30 minutes

member.name: P:Amazon.TimestreamInfluxDB.Model.InfluxDBv2Parameters.StorageSeriesFileMaxConcurrentSnapshotCompactions
member.summary:

Maximum number of snapshot compactions that can run concurrently across all series partitions in a database.
Default: 0

member.name: P:Amazon.TimestreamInfluxDB.Model.InfluxDBv2Parameters.StorageSeriesIdSetCacheSize
member.summary:

Size of the internal cache used in the TSI index to store previously calculated series results. member.name: P:Amazon.TimestreamInfluxDB.Model.InfluxDBv2Parameters.StorageWalMaxConcurrentWrites
member.summary:

Maximum number writes to the WAL directory to attempt at the same time. Setting this value to 0 results in number of processing units available x2.
Default: 0

member.name: P:Amazon.TimestreamInfluxDB.Model.InfluxDBv2Parameters.StorageWalMaxWriteDelay
member.summary:

Maximum amount of time a write request to the WAL directory will wait when the maximum number of concurrent active writes to the WAL directory has been met. Set to 0 to disable the timeout.
Default: 10 minutes

Enable tracing in InfluxDB and specifies the tracing type. Tracing is disabled by default.
